    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# CLO3 Graph Fix: Decision Tree and Cluster Graph\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook adds the required decision tree graph and cluster graph using the Student Performance Factors dataset. The explanations are kept simple so the results can be understood and explained clearly."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier, plot_tree\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score\n",
        "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "df = pd.read_csv('StudentPerformanceFactors.csv')\n",
        "df.head()\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Decision Tree Graph\n",
        "\n",
        "The decision tree is used to classify students into Low, Medium, or High performance levels based on their exam score. It uses simple variables that are easy to explain: Hours Studied, Attendance, Sleep Hours, and Previous Scores."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "df['Performance_Level'] = pd.cut(\n",
        "    df['Exam_Score'],\n",
        "    bins=[0, 65, 75, 101],\n",
        "    labels=['Low', 'Medium', 'High']\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "X = df[['Hours_Studied', 'Attendance', 'Sleep_Hours', 'Previous_Scores']]\n",
        "y = df['Performance_Level']\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
        "    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=1\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "tree_model = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=3, random_state=1)\n",
        "tree_model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "y_pred = tree_model.predict(X_test)\n",
        "print('Decision Tree Accuracy:', accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))\n",
        "plot_tree(\n",
        "    tree_model,\n",
        "    feature_names=X.columns,\n",
        "    class_names=['Low', 'Medium', 'High'],\n",
        "    filled=True,\n",
        "    rounded=True\n",
        ")\n",
        "plt.title('Decision Tree Graph for Student Performance')\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Decision Tree Explanation\n",
        "\n",
        "The decision tree graph shows how the model classifies students into Low, Medium, or High performance levels. Each box in the tree represents a decision rule. For example, the tree may split students based on Previous Scores, Attendance, or Hours Studied.\n",
        "\n",
        "This graph is useful because it shows the prediction process step by step. It also helps explain which factors are important when predicting student performance."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Cluster Graph\n",
        "\n",
        "K-Means clustering is used to group students based on similar values. In this graph, the variables used are Hours Studied and Exam Score because they are simple and easy to understand visually."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "cluster_data = df[['Hours_Studied', 'Exam_Score']]\n",
        "\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "cluster_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(cluster_data)\n",
        "\n",
        "kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3, random_state=1, n_init=10)\n",
        "df['Cluster'] = kmeans.fit_predict(cluster_scaled)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))\n",
        "plt.scatter(\n",
        "    df['Hours_Studied'],\n",
        "    df['Exam_Score'],\n",
        "    c=df['Cluster']\n",
        ")\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Hours Studied')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Exam Score')\n",
        "plt.title('K-Means Cluster Graph: Hours Studied vs Exam Score')\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "cluster_summary = df.groupby('Cluster')[['Hours_Studied', 'Exam_Score']].mean()\n",
        "cluster_summary\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Cluster Graph Explanation\n",
        "\n",
        "The cluster graph shows groups of students based on Hours Studied and Exam Score. Each color represents a different cluster. Students in the same cluster have similar study hours and exam scores.\n",
        "\n",
        "This graph is useful because it helps identify patterns in the dataset. For example, one cluster may represent students with lower study hours and lower exam scores, while another cluster may represent students with higher study hours and higher exam scores."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Proper Usage of AI\n",
        "\n",
        "AI was used as a support tool to help organize the code and improve the explanations. The graphs and results were generated from the actual dataset using Python. The explanations were kept simple so the results can be understood and discussed clearly."
      ]
    }
